Nice little taco/burrito take-out at 16th & Harvard NW. My son had a beef taco, I had a couple of carnitas, & my wife had a quesadilla. The carnitas tacos were good but a bit bland, the beef taco was a bit salty, and my wife thought the quesadilla good. Some others coming in purchased got some very good looking tacos, so perhaps our simple choices as first timers weren't the best. Pica Taco is everything you'd expect from a whole in the wall taco shop. The food is good with a lot of options. The tacos are served in a more authentic fashion that I enjoy with corn tortillas, meat, all the sauce your heart desires, some cilantro, some onions, and some radishes. Reminds me of what you can get in California.  The burritos are solid. The nachos are on point.  Only downside for me is it is a little pricey, but that may just be me being picky about what I used to pay in other places.  Overall, good food, good portion, good sauces, good place
